<subSubSection pageId="65" pageNumber="66" type="remarks">
<paragraph pageId="65" pageNumber="66">Remarks.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="65" pageNumber="66">
<bibRefCitation author="Lepeletier, ALM" journalOrPublisher="Annales du Museum National d'Histoire Naturelle" pageId="74" pageNumber="75" pagination="115 - 129" title="Memoire sur quelques especes nouvelles d'insectes de la section des Hymenopteres appeles les Portetuyaux, et sur les caracteres de cette famille et des genres qui la composent." volume="7" year="1806">Lepeletier (1806)</bibRefCitation>
described 
<taxonomicName authority="Latreille, 1806" authorityName="Latreille" authorityYear="1806" class="Insecta" family="Chrysididae" genus="Hedychrum" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Hedychrum nitidum" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="65" pageNumber="66" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nitidum">Hedychrum nitidum</taxonomicName>
based on a male, but the description is obviously based on a female. The original colour drawing (pl. 6: 6) clearly shows a specimen with ovipositor tube. Moreover, the colour given in the description likely referres to a female. In the Spinola collection there are two females, possibly syntypes. At MNHN, there are other specimens of this species coming from 
<normalizedToken originalValue="Lepeletier’s">Lepeletier's</normalizedToken>
collection, included some syntypes (
<bibRefCitation author="Buysson, R du" journalOrPublisher="Annales de la Societe Entomologique de France" pageId="71" pageNumber="72" pagination="518 - 580" title="Etude des Chrysidides du Museum de Paris." volume="66" year="1898">du Buysson 1898</bibRefCitation>
: 563, as a synonym of 
<taxonomicName authority="Dahlbom, 1845" authorityName="Dahlbom" authorityYear="1845" class="Insecta" family="Chrysididae" genus="Holopyga" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Holopyga fervida" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="65" pageNumber="66" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="fervida">Holopyga fervida</taxonomicName>
, currently in box 11 of the general collection).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
